## Architecture

```
Internet
  │  HTTPS 443 / HTTP 80   (host-bound by nginx-reverse-proxy, with HTTP/2)
  ▼
nginx-reverse-proxy (nginx:1.28-alpine, ports 80/443)
  │  routes by Host header; unknown hosts on :80 return 444
  ├─ wcma.work          ──► mapnj2:3001       (Next.js)
  ├─ xyz.wcma.work      ──► xyz:3002          (Next.js XYZ tile server)
  ├─ pozi.wcma.work     ──► qgis-server:80    (WMS — what the Flutter app uses)
  ├─ parcels.wcma.work  ──► qgis-server:80    (WMS, MAP-pinned to wimmera_parcels.qgz)
  └─ wfml.wcma.work     ──► /ows/ → qgis-server:80
                          ──► /     → lizmap-nginx:80 → lizmap (PHP-FPM)
```

All containers share the `internal-apps` Docker network (the reverse-proxy container also joins `reverse-proxy_default` to expose host ports).

